---
// Temporary design-system preview. The real home page comes next, after review.
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Nicolas Tabet">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Nicolas Tabet</h1>
  <p>
    Systems-focused engineer. I work close to the metal — C, computer
    architecture, and the infrastructure that runs underneath everything else.
    Right now I'm a TA for Purdue's CS240 and heading to Columbia for an
    <a href="/about">MSCS in software systems</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Type hierarchy</h2>
  <p>
    This block only exists so the design system is reviewable. The body sits at
    a comfortable reading measure with generous line-height, one accent color
    for <a href="/">links</a>, and a restrained neutral palette that flips with
    <code>prefers-color-scheme</code>.
  </p>

  <h3>A third-level heading</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Generous whitespace, text-first layout.</li>
    <li>Self-hosted Inter, preloaded, zero third-party requests.</li>
    <li>No JavaScript shipped on this page.</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    Restraint is a feature. The content does the work.
  </blockquote>

  <pre><code>int main(void) &#123;
    write(1, "hello\n", 6);
    return 0;
&#125;</code></pre>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
